His hands are heavy slow.

266
00:23:00,460 --> 00:23:06,470
Suddenly Ali is quick and strong again.

267
00:23:06,470 --> 00:23:11,019
He hits his opponent again and again.

268
00:23:11,019 --> 00:23:14,529
And suddenly Foreman is on the floor.

269
00:23:14,529 --> 00:23:18,450
He can't stand up.

270
00:23:18,450 --> 00:23:20,149
Ali is dancing.

271
00:23:20,149 --> 00:23:22,140
He is the world champion again.

272
00:23:22,140 --> 00:23:28,860
He is the world champion again.

273
00:23:28,860 --> 00:23:33,710
Ali stayed the champion for six years.

274
00:23:33,710 --> 00:23:43,830
He beat Joe Frazier again in Manila in 1975
after a long and difficult fight.

275
00:23:43,830 --> 00:23:52,320
In 1978, Ali lost a fight with Leon Spinks
in Las Vegas.

276
00:23:52,320 --> 00:23:58,280
But then, seven months later, he beat him.

277
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:06,470
Ali was the new world champion three times
in fourteen years.

